Class EnumRowMapper<T extends Enum<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.zethmayr.benjamin.spring.common.model.base.ModelTrusted<InvertibleRowMapperBase>
      • net.zethmayr.benjamin.spring.common.mapper.base.InvertibleRowMapperBase<T>
        • net.zethmayr.benjamin.spring.common.mapper.base.EnumRowMapper<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The mapped enum.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    InvertibleRowMapper<T>, org.springframework.jdbc.core.RowMapper<T>

    public abstract class EnumRowMapper<T extends Enum<T>>
extends InvertibleRowMapperBase<T>
    A row mapper for tables which reflect enums - writing is as normal, but reading is id-only and materializes as the preexisting instance by ordinal. This exists to support referential integrity for ad-hoc queries.
